          "distinct": true,
          "id": "450c25b2241ea30af44098d26a505b05b92f74bb",
          "message": "fix(bip324): zeroize sk on early return + fix destructor secure-erase (BPS-1..8)\n\nBUG-3 — complete_handshake all-zero early return without zeroizing sk:\n  Bip324Session::complete_handshake() builds sk=fast::Scalar::from_bytes(privkey_)\n  on the stack. If ECDH returns all-zero (attacker-crafted peer encoding),\n  the early 'return false' left sk un-wiped. Fix: detail::secure_erase(&sk,\n  sizeof(sk)) immediately before the return false on the all_zero path.\n  Also: proactive privkey_ erase added on the success path before established_=true.\n\nBUG-4 — ~Bip324Session volatile loop vs detail::secure_erase:\n  Destructor used a raw volatile uint8_t* loop, missing the\n  atomic_signal_fence(memory_order_seq_cst) barrier that Bip324Cipher::~Bip324Cipher\n  already had via detail::secure_erase. Fix: use detail::secure_erase consistently.\n\nTests: test_regression_bip324_session (BPS-1..8) wired into unified_audit_runner\nunder section memory_safety. Standalone: pass=36 fail=0.\nCAAS Stage 0 (check_exploit_wiring.py): PASS.",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:29:09Z",
