          "distinct": true,
          "id": "8c910657bd0d821217d40a6e676bf6f43d72092d",
          "message": "feat(scan): batch_scan_run_lockstep — b_scan digits loop once over all A_i\n\nN-stream lockstep: outer loop over 128 wNAF digit positions (b_scan computed\nonce), inner loop over chunk_n accumulators (default chunk_size=256, L2-fit).\n\nKey wins over sequential per-point shamir_2stream_glv52:\n  - Zero-digit positions (~75%): skip chunk_n inner iterations with ONE branch\n  - Sign branch hoisted outside inner loop for non-zero digits\n  - 256-point chunk working set: ~327KB tables + ~30KB accumulators → L2\n\nBench mode [J] (16T + LUT + lockstep):\n  [D] baseline (no LUT):  3887 ns/op  0.26 M/s\n  [J] lockstep+LUT:       3567 ns/op  0.28 M/s  (+8.5% over [D])\n  Validation: 0xeccf8f305e69b840 ✓\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-25T14:07:43Z",
          "tree_id": "6eb8449a22a587a3e8f93d4ff0ee963281055b52",
          "url": "https://github.com/shrec/UltrafastSecp256k1/commit/8c910657bd0d821217d40a6e676bf6f43d72092d"
