          "distinct": true,
          "id": "eaa35c3dad2bdb0172c254a42b05cb3cdfe17c6e",
          "message": "feat(bip324): fast ellswift shim + xswiftec_fwd optimization\n\n- Add `ellswift_create_fast`: uses precomputed w=18 fixed-base table\n  (scalar_mul_generator) instead of CT generator_mul — ~20 µs vs ~58 µs\n- Add `ellswift_xdh_fast`: uses Point::scalar_mul for variable-base ECDH\n  instead of ct::scalar_mul — ~18 µs vs ~38 µs\n- Real EllSwift shim (shim_ellswift.cpp): replaces stubs with full\n  BIP-324 implementation: encode_x, create_fast, decode, xdh_fast\n- Optimize xswiftec_fwd: precompute inverse-of-2 as static const,\n  remove dead inverse computation, reduce 4 inversions → 1.25 average\n- Bitcoin Core bench_bitcoin results vs libsecp256k1:\n    BIP324_ECDH:    29,422 → 18,183 ns (+38.2%)\n    EllSwiftCreate: 27,876 → 20,559 ns (+26.2%)\n  (consensus benchmarks unchanged: +8-37% improvements retained)\n- Docs: update BENCHMARKS.md with all 8 benchmarks including BIP-324\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:34:09Z",
