          "distinct": true,
          "id": "421a94ad71005acd370882903df95e8e8aca6e28",
          "message": "feat(caas): PARSE_RETVAL_IGNORED checker + Clang SA + GCC -fanalyzer workflows\n\nThree hardening additions for Bitcoin Core PR readiness:\n\n1. dev_bug_scanner.py: new PARSE_RETVAL_IGNORED checker (HIGH severity)\n   - Detects Scalar::parse_bytes_strict_nonzero / parse_bytes_strict calls\n     whose bool return is silently discarded (output Scalar indeterminate).\n   - Grounded in two bugs fixed in fast_scan_batch (2026-04-26) and one in\n     compute_a_eff (address.cpp:804, this commit).\n   - Zero false positives on current codebase.\n\n2. .github/workflows/clang-sa.yml: Clang Static Analyzer (scan-build-18)\n   - Inter-procedural symbolic execution; catches cross-function null-deref\n     and uninitialized-read paths that clang-tidy misses.\n   - Runs on push/PR to main/dev and weekly (Monday 04:00 UTC).\n   - Alpha checkers: ArrayBoundV2, ReturnPtrRange, UninitializedObject.\n\n3. .github/workflows/gcc-analyzer.yml: GCC 14 -fanalyzer\n   - Different SE engine; CWE-mapped findings complement Clang SA.\n   - Weekly + push/PR trigger; non-blocking advisory run in addition to\n     the hard gate.\n\n4. address.cpp:804 — fixed unchecked parse_bytes_strict_nonzero return in\n   compute_a_eff (unit scalar 1; always succeeds but explicitly checked).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-26T10:35:03Z",
          "tree_id": "de8c6e2ef499cd1dd35be6e0207fcd01db422a81",
